-- Toyota Q1 global sales fall 27%
-- 
-- Thu Apr 23, 2009 12:44am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/23/us-toyota-sales-idUSTRE53M10W20090423

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) said on Thursday its groupwide global vehicle sales fell 27 percent in January-March from a year earlier to 1.767 million units. 

 For the parent only, which excludes trucks and cars sold by subsidiaries Hino Motors Ltd ( 7205.T ) and Daihatsu Motor Co ( 7262.T ), sales fell 28 percent to 1.53 million units, a Toyota spokesman said. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )